LPmud BUGS / issue tracker
Last reviewed: 2026-03-09

ACTIVE / MEANINGFUL

- query_weight() self-destruct recursion hazard:
  If query_weight() destructs the current object, transfer/destruct paths can
  recurse until recursion limits trigger. Current behavior is still hazardous
  (now typically "Too deep recursion" rather than an immediate driver crash).
  Keep this as an active robustness issue.

- Runtime/debug errors are not consistently mirrored to wizard logs:
  Some compile/parser errors are mirrored, but many runtime/debug-only messages
  still do not reach wizard-facing logs.

- struct lnode model remains cast-heavy:
  The "single struct + many specialized structs" design is still in place.
  A union-based representation is still valid technical debt.

- Predefined identifier lookup is not hash-based:
  Lookup is still table/binary-search based. This is a cleanup/perf debt item.

- Static string_space table still exists:
  String interning (stralloc) is used, but a static string_space table is still
  present. Dynamic-only consolidation is still pending.

LEGACY / CONTEXT-DEPENDENT

- malloc.c free-list recombination scheduling:
  Relevant only when using legacy MALLOC=malloc builds. Default builds use
  MALLOC=sysalloc, so this is not a default-runtime issue.

- "Programming language should be better documented":
  Largely historical. Documentation exists across mudlib/doc, but quality and
  coverage can still be improved as normal maintenance.

- "Too much inflation in the game":
  Mudlib economy/game-design concern, not a core driver defect.

FEATURE REQUESTS (NOT BUGS)

- Add TFTP protocol for wizard file transfer.

UNVERIFIED LEGACY NOTE

- "Search pattern /*/ in ed will hang":
  Not reproduced in current quick checks. Keep as unverified until a dedicated
  in-driver ed reproduction confirms or disproves.

CLOSED / STALE NOTE

- "All calls to xalloc() should be replaced ...":
  Historical/incomplete note. xalloc is intentionally used as the allocator
  wrapper in current code.
